Installation instruction for Linux operation system
===================================================

I. Install and remove application
=================================

1. Install
----------

a. Install from binary '.tar.gz' package

    # cp tubes2-trial-2.0.2-i586.tar.gz /opt
    # cd /opt
    # tar -xzf tubes2-trial-2.0.2-i586.tar.gz
    # cd tubes2-trial
    # ./create_links
    
                or

    # tar -xzf tubes2-trial-2.0.2-i586.tar.gz
    # cd tubes2-trial
    # ./install

b. Install from '.bin' package

    # ./tubes2-trial-2.0.2-i586.bin

c. Install from '.deb' package

    # dpkg -i tubes2-trial_2.0.2-1_i386.deb

d. Install from '.rpm' package

    # rpm -i tubes2-trial-2.0.2-1.i586.rpm

e. Install from source
     
    # tar -xzf tubes2-trial-2.0.2.tar.gz
    # cd tubes2-trial
    # ./configure
    # make
    # make install

2. Remove
---------

a. If you have installed from binary '.tar.gz' package

    # /opt/tubes2-trial/remove_links
    # rm -r /opt/tubes2-trial/

            vagy

    # /opt/tubes2-trial/uninstall

b. If you have installed from '.bin' package

    # /opt/tubes2-trial/uninstall

c. If you have installed from '.deb' package

    # dpkg -r tubes2-trial

d. If you have installed from '.rpm' package

    # rpm -e tubes2-trial

e. If you have installed from source

    # cd tubes2-trial
    # make uninstall

II. Install and remove language package
=======================================

1. Install
----------

a. Install from '.tar.gz' package

    # tar -xzf tubes2-trial-??-2.0.2-all.tar.gz
    # cd tubes2-trial-??
    # ./install

b. Install from '.bin' package

    # ./tubes2-trial-??-2.0.2-all.bin

c. Install from '.deb' package

    # dpkg -i tubes2-trial-??_2.0.2-1_all.deb

d. Install from '.rpm' package

    # rpm -i tubes2-trial-??-2.0.2-1.noarch.rpm

e. Install from source
     
    # tar -xzf tubes2-trial-??-2.0.2.tar.gz
    # cd tubes2-trial-??
    # ./configure
    # make
    # make install

2. Remove
---------

a. If you have installed from '.deb' package

    # dpkg -r tubes2-trial-??

b. If you have installed from '.rpm' package

    # rpm -e tubes2-trial-??

c. If you have installed from source

    # cd tubes2-trial-??
    # make uninstall

